<p>By default, xterm uses the black-on-white colour scheme. Being of the
old-school type, I like my xterm to use green-on-black. Here's how to do it:
</p>
<!-- break -->
<p><tt>
$ vi ~/.Xdefaults<br><br><br>
~/.Xdefaults<br><br>
XTerm*background:black<br>
XTerm*foreground:green<br>
XTerm*loginShell:true<br>
<br><br><br>
$ xrdb -load ~/.Xdefaults<br>
</p>

